reviews.review_text: Interesting Show I was there, and enroute to Red Rocks....the second set statrted out very hot with The Other One, but tension got high when Brent did "I Don't Need Love Anymore" when Jerry was looking for drums...so Jerry walked off during the song.  When space was over Jerry must have felt bad for his part in the tension (after all Brent was going throught some tough times on the home front)  and came out of space into a rare It's Nobody's Fault But Mine".  A very hot Comes a Time put the cherry on top.

This one sounds good, compare to Oade... Nice show, a comment on the sound quality, to my ears, a little clearer than the Oade, and also the Oade has a too loud kick drum sound. Compare the two before downloading. Cheers. I LOVE '80-'87! More!!!
phuckinmissinhim This is a gr8 show to grab a jar and get lost in a wonderful sounding mix!!!!love the "comes a time" just popped in to say "high" see ya kids roundandround!!

Smokin! Hot diggety dog that Stranger is Hot!  I'm not even past that and I had to write a comment.  I saw this show and have listened to the old cassette tape many times but not for years.  It's great to hear it again.

I Don't Need Love & Jerry Jerry didn't play on any of the I Don't Loves that I saw. I don't think that he was playing Nobody's Fault for Mine for Brent (see review previous). He just realized the song sucked and didn't want to play on it.
